checkers.util

Class QualifierPolymorphism

  • java.lang.Object
    • checkers.util.QualifierPolymorphism

  • public class QualifierPolymorphism
extends Object
    Implements framework support for type qualifier polymorphism. Checkers that wish to use it should add calls to annotate(MethodInvocationTree, AnnotatedTypeMirror.AnnotatedExecutableType) to the AnnotatedTypeFactory.annotateImplicit(Tree, AnnotatedTypeMirror) and AnnotatedTypeFactory.annotateImplicit(Tree, AnnotatedTypeMirror) methods.

    This implementation currently only supports polymorphism for method invocations, for which the return type depends on the unification of the parameter/receiver types.

    See Also:
    PolymorphicQualifier
